Currently, users can only be created in internal directories (Delegated or Stash Internal) depending on which directory in index position 0 (top directory). FishEye allows this functionality (see attached image).

{quote}
... we could not create a user (with LDAP credential) as Stash administrator, just like what we could do in Fisheye/Crucible. Instead we have to ask a user to log into the Stash instance first to become a stash user.
{quote}

Stash pull request (and possibly other?) emails are sent as

{noformat}
Content-type: text/html; charset=UTF-8
{noformat}

To accommodate those of us who prefer plain text over HTML, please consider changing this to multipart/alternative and having a text/plain and text/html section.

Changing user preferences and/or deleting repositories fails:

{noformat}
Unable to create filter
com.atlassian.util.concurrent.LazyReference$InitializationException: java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: Could not initialize class com.sun.xml.bind.v2.model.impl.RuntimeModelBuilder
{noformat}

*Workaround: Upgrade Java to at least 1.6.0_4*

*Rating*: :) Good

{panel:title=What do you like?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#c2ffa2|bgColor=#fff}
.
{panel}

{panel:title=What needs to be improved?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#faacad|bgColor=#fff}
The "notifications workbox" icon in Stash keyboard shortcut is inconsistant with Confluence

Confluence is G+N (go to notifications) 

Looks like Stash has done G+I ... why create a new pattern? Can we stick with the same one for cross-product consistency 

{panel}

Hi, today my search button for one of the repos started to answer "An error occurred while listing the files. The files listed may not be complete."

I found exception in log and it is in attach.

Also, I found this exception in sources:

log.error(String.format(
        "Error occurred while streaming file listing '%s' at path '%s' at revision '%s'",
        repository.getName(),
        path,
        objectId
), e);

KeyedMessage errorMessage = i18nService.getKeyedText(
        "stash.rest.filelist.error",
        "An error occurred while listing the files. The files listed may not be complete.");
if (!new RestErrors(errorMessage.getLocalisedMessage()).endScopeAndTryWriteTo(writer)) {
    log.debug("Unable to add the 'error' property to the streamed JSON file listing: " + errorMessage.getRootMessage());
}


And also, I tried to re-send get-request:
https://our.server.address/rest/api/latest/projects/STARDUST/repos/browser/files?limit=100000&at=refs%2Fheads%2Fmaster
It returns JSON with 
"errors":[{"context":null,"message":"An error occurred while listing the files. The files listed may not be complete.","exceptionName":null} 
on the end, but all the files are included (seems to be)

but! if you change limit to 99999 it will return valid JSON with 99999 files

*Rating*: :( Bad

{panel:title=What do you like?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#c2ffa2|bgColor=#fff}
Getting to relevant commits from JIRA
{panel}

{panel:title=What needs to be improved?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#faacad|bgColor=#fff}
Not being able to get from JIRA to the relevant pull request.  (Including, cannot get from commit to relevant pull request) (which I already raised once today, but this is a totally different use-case)
{panel}

*Rating*: ;) Meh!

{panel:title=What do you like?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#c2ffa2|bgColor=#fff}
Looking at code in a pull request
{panel}

{panel:title=What needs to be improved?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#faacad|bgColor=#fff}
Suddenly discovering that because I'm looking at a specific commit of a pull request, I'm no longer in a pull request context.  

One of the nice things about DVCSes is that they make commits cheap, and people can split their work into nice logical commits.  Stash's pull requests hide these nice logical commits, and if I click through to them I actually _exit_ the pull request until I press "back" on the browser.  

And I can't comment on the commits.
{panel}

{quote}
We need a solution that supports a replicated solution (master master replication fronted with HAProxy) because we cannot have a single DB point of failure.
{quote}

{quote}
We are doing basic mysql replication like this http://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.5/en/replication.html. We need some sort of redundant solution for the database because we are a worldwide organization with 24/7 development.
{quote}

*Rating*: :) Good

{panel:title=What do you like?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#c2ffa2|bgColor=#fff}
Being able to delete branch on merge.
{panel}

{panel:title=What needs to be improved?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#faacad|bgColor=#fff}
Merge dialog seemed to take forever to close.

Had the 'Delete branch' checked, clicked 'Merge' and the dialog stayed there for quite a while (at least 10 seconds, Merge button was greyed out)

Opened new tab to check if the merge had been successful (and it had). Went back to tab and the dialog was still there.

Only after clicking on the 'Give Feedback' did the dialog close.

Not sure if it was just taking a long time, or if clicking on the grey area was what triggered the dialog to close.
{panel}

{code:java}
i18nService.getText("", "bla-bla ' \{0\}", "bla")
{code} 
returns bla-bla' \{0\} 
but 

i18nService.getText("", "bla-bla \{0\}", "bla") 
returns bla-bla bla

*Rating*: ;) Meh!

{panel:title=What do you like?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#c2ffa2|bgColor=#fff}
Stuff
{panel}

{panel:title=What needs to be improved?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#faacad|bgColor=#fff}
The notificaiton box at the top right only shows me PRs that  I have to review.  It would be nice if you could also quickly access PRs there that you have openend and are still waiting to be reviewed by other people.

The number badge can still only show the number of PRs that are waiting for your review, but once you open the dropdown I think we should also show links to PRs that you created and are still open.
{panel}

*Rating*: :) Good

{panel:title=What do you like?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#c2ffa2|bgColor=#fff}
I like that new commits unapprove the PR
{panel}

{panel:title=What needs to be improved?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#faacad|bgColor=#fff}
Merges from master should _not_ unapprove the PR.  (And they should be possible from the PR UI, but I've filed that before :) )
{panel}

